  <title>GLib.Regex.prototype.replace_literal</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function replace_literal(string: Array(String), start_position: Number(gint), replacement: String, match_options: <link xref="GLib.RegexMatchFlags">GLib.RegexMatchFlags</link>): String {
    // Gjs wrapper for g_regex_replace_literal()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Replaces all occurrences of the pattern in <code>regex</code> with the
replacement text. <code>replacement</code> is replaced literally, to
include backreferences use <link xref="GLib.Regex.replace"/>.</p>  <p>Setting <code>start_position</code> differs from just passing over a
shortened string and setting #G_REGEX_MATCH_NOTBOL in the
case of a pattern that begins with any kind of lookbehind
assertion, such as "\b".</p>
  <p>Since 2.14</p>
